social_posts.post_text:
A wholesome foodie Sunday 🥕🥬🥒🍠
1. Abundance
2. Veggies for gut health
3. Lunch
4. Balance
5. The best combo
6. Coffee + pecan loaf
7. A hack for keeping herbs fresh
eating 30 plant foods per week has shown to have significant positive effects on the microbiome - here’s some inspo of what your gut needs to thrive 🥬🍠🍅🥗🫑🧅🧄

reminder: fat does not make you ‘fat’.
our bodies (specifically our gut & hormones!) rely on good types of fats to function and thrive. and when our gut is happy we feel energised, clear headed and satisfied 😌

in my bowl today:
- oats
- chia seeds
- full fat yoghurt
- almond butter
- crushed walnuts
- cacao nibs
- apples
- banana
- hemp seeds

have a good day (: #strengthandsalad

HOMEMADE FLU TONIC 🤧 my go-to warming elixir when I feel the start of a cold, no medicines required! Don’t be scared by the raw garlic, this is what makes this drink so effective - I mince it really fine and just swallow whole (which also stops any bad breath occurring 😷). sip or shot, whichever takes your fancy. take every 4-6 hours for relief 😌 

- juice of 1 lemon
- 1/4 tsp raw garlic (minced)
- 1/4 tsp ginger (finely chopped)
- 1/4 tsp turmeric
- 1 tsp honey
- 1/2 cup warm water

#strengthandsalad

nutty, salty, chocolatey, sweet and full of good fats and fibre for gut health and happy hormones. pair with yoghurt, plant milk or just eat a handful on its own 😋

SALTED CHOCOLATE GRANOLA
- 150g oats
- 25g cacao nibs
- 50g roughly chopped almonds
- 50g roughly chopped peanuts
- 50g roughly chopped hazelnuts
- 50g roughly chopped walnuts
- 1 tsp sea salt
- 3 tbsp coconut oil
- 6 tbsp maple syrup
- 4 tbsp cacao powder

Pre heat oven to 160c. Mix the oats, nibs, nuts and salt in a large bowl. Melt the coconut oil, maple syrup and cacao powder in a pan, add to the bowl and stir well. Lay flat on a baking tray and bake for 20 minutes. Store in an airtight container for up to a week. #strengthandsalad

GREEN GODESS TOAST 🥑🌱💚
this basil cream took my regular avo toast to a whole new level! please make a.s.a.p!

- 30g basil (roughly chopped)
- 2 tbsp yoghurt
- 1 tbsp tahini
- 1/2 tsp sea salt
- Juice 1/2 lemon

mix everything together and spread generously onto toasted sourdough. add avocado, micro herbs, hemp seeds, salt + pepper. #strengthandsalad

10-minute gut health ramen 🍜 loaded with pre-biotic veggies, moorish noddles, and nourishing broth which means better digestion and healthier hormones 🤍

to make:
- 300ml chicken broth
- 60g rice noodles
- small handful of sliced mushrooms
- 1 clove minced garlic
- 1 tbsp tamari
- 1 tbsp fresh herbs
- small handful spinach 
- 2 tbsp edamame beans
- toppings: hard boiled egg, black sesame seeds
simmer everything in a pan for 8 minutes until the flavours have married together. add to a bowl, top with a jammy egg and a drizzle of toasted sesame oil and voila. #strengthandsalad

MATCHA GREEN TEA 💚🍵🪀🧩 my favourite colour but also one of my favourite superfood drinks for these reasons...
⠀ 
1. this delicate green powder tastes buttery, aromatic and amazing in a latte.
⠀ 
2. making a cup has become a relaxing daily ritual i perform to help manage stress.
⠀ 
3. it gives me a gentle energy boost without a caffeine spike and crash thanks to the amino acid l-theanine.
⠀ 
4. it increases alpha brain waves resulting in an alert yet calm and relaxed mind.
⠀ 
5. it's also packed with antioxidants that neutralise harmful toxins in the body leading to brighter skin, better digestion, a happier mood, more energy, and less mental stress.
⠀ 
sign me up for 10 million gallons please!
⠀ 
in the glass 👉 blend or whisk 1 tsp @clearspringuk with 1/4 cup cold water and 1/2 cup hot water (this stops the matcha from burning and becoming bitter). pour into a mug or heat proof glass and top with warm foamy oat milk. happy drinking! 🍵💚 #strengthandsalad

PREBIOTIC BREAKFAST 🍄 feeding the good gut bugs this morning with creamy mushrooms on crunchy sourdough. this combo is honestly insanely delicious!

1 tsp olive oil
100g mushrooms
1 small clove garlic (minced)
1/2 tsp salt
crack of black pepper
1/2 tsp dried oregano
1 tbsp fresh dill
1 heaped tbsp yoghurt
1 tsp dijon mustard

add oil, mushrooms, salt, pepper and oregano to a pan. cover and cook on a medium heat for 5 minutes until mushrooms are soft. once cooked take off heat and add the yoghurt, mustard and dill. spoon on top of toasted sourdough slathered in protein rich hummus for extra goodness. #strengthandsalad

FERTILITY NUTRITION 👶 after spending all of my teenage years and early 20s with irregular periods, hormonal imbalances and suspected PCOS, reproductive health has always been front of my mind.

i remember speaking to a doctor about my fertility concerns. she asked me “are you thinking of starting a family soon?”. I answered “no” and she replied “well then there’s nothing we can do right now.”

the reality is it’s never too early to start thinking about fertility. luckily i ignored that doctor’s advice and started my own gut healing and hormone balancing journey and thankfully starting a family turned out to be straightforward 🙏.

here‘s what I did;
- widening plant foods to 30 a week
- increasing oily fish
- focused on eating fertility nutrients like selenium, zinc, iodine, vitamin d, vitamin c, b vitamins
- supported my liver for proper hormone clearance
- prioritised meditation, self care activities and relaxation for stress management 
- worked with a nutritionist for advice on fertility supplements 
- only used natural skincare and cleaning products to lower toxin exposure 

regardless of whether or not you want kids, good fertility is a sign of overall good health so it’s something we should all be striving for 🤍 #strengthandsald

EASY NUT BUTTER STUFFED DATES IN A CHOCOLATE SHELL 🍫🥜🌰 // think of these as your very own assortment box of chocolates - except they’re blood sugar balancing (for healthy hormones!), full of fibre and incredibly good for you!

all you need is;
- pitted dates
- peanut butter 
- de-shelled peanuts (whole)
- dark chocolate 
- coconut oil 
- toppings: desiccated coconut, crushed pistachios, flaked almonds, chopped peanuts

split each date in half and add a spoon of nut butter and one peanut. melt about 100g dark chocolate with 2 tsp coconut oil. cover each date and sprinkle with your topping of choice. freeze for 30 minutes. keep refrigerated for up to a week. #strengthandsalad

1-2-1 NUTRITION CONSULTATIONS // get personalised nutrition advice, supplement guidance, meal plans and recipes to improve your gut health for good.

more info and how to book in my bio! #strengthandsalad

NOURISHING CHOCOLATEY PANCAKES 🥞 this recipe is proof that indulgent, delicious meals can in fact be nutritious. enjoy :)

(makes 4 large pancakes)
100g oats 
1 heaped tbsp cacao powder
1 tsp baking powder
2 tbsp full fat thick yoghurt
100ml almond milk
1 egg
2 tbsp dark chocolate chips (optional)

blend the oats and cacao powder to make a flour mix then stir in the other ingredients until a thick batter has formed. split the mixture 4 ways and fry in a knob of coconut oil on a medium heat for 3-4 minutes on each side. serve with fresh strawberries and a dollop of yoghurt. #strengthandsalad

My favourite kind of dinner! Wholesome ingredients, rich in flavour, makes extra portions for efficiency, and cooking + clean up all done in under 30 minutes 🍜

(Serves 4)

Ingredients:
* 1 tbsp coconut oil
* 1 medium onion
* 1 tsp sea salt
* 3 medium garlic cloves
* 3 tbsp laksa paste 
* 400ml coconut milk
* 1 tsp turmeric
* 3 cups veg (i did broccoli, peas and butternut squash ) 
* 200g tofu
* 1 Litre vegetable stock
* 120g dried rice noodles

How to:
1. Fry onion, garlic and salt in coconut oil on a medium heat for about 5 minutes.
2. Add laksa paste, coconut milk, turmeric and stir well. 
3. Add the veg and cook for 10 minutes until nearly soft.
4. Then add the tofu, stick and noodles for the final few minutes.
5. Serve with fresh herbs, black sesame seeds, and a squeeze of lime juice.

*My top tip: use frozen pre-chopped veggies for convenience and time-saving

The hack I’ve been using for years! 🥛☕️ here’s my budget friendly and super easy way of creating the foamiest milk at home!

Ingredients:
* 1/4 cup milk (I used cashew milk)
* 1/4 tsp coconut oil (this helps to thicken the milk)
* 1/4 cup boiling water

How to make:
1. Add everything to a French press and stir well
2. Replace the lid then slowly begin to pump the plunger
3. After a few seconds increase the speed to really aerate the milk
4. Pour over coffee, matcha, turmeric latte - whatever you like to drink (:

SEA SALT BANANA BREAD with the bounciest sponge and most delicious crust 🤤 my top baking hack since having my son is using pre-made baking mixes. anything that reduces my time in the kitchen but still delivers a delicious healthy bake is something my tired mum-brain craves 😄

How to: 
1. heat the oven to 180c fan.
2. in a large bowl mash 2 really ripe bananas, add 1 egg, 60g of melted butter, 1 tsp cinnamon, 1 tsp baking powder and mix really well.
3. add the baking mix (I used the @creativenature banana bread mix) and stir well again.
4. grease a loaf tin with coconut oil or butter and pour in the mix.
5. bake for 30-40 minutes (or until a knife comes out clean).
6. sprinkle with flaky sea salt whilst hot. enjoy!

Let’s talk supplements 💊 even with a nutrient rich diet and a well functioning gut it’s still incredibly hard to get good levels of certain nutrients. I’ve listed the top 3 nutrients I take everyday that are essential for glowing skin, a happy microbiome, bounds of energy, good sleep and just overall health. 

Hope you find this helpful 🫶🏼
#strengthandsalad

15-MINUTE SMOKY SAUSAGE & LENTIL SOUP 🥣 lately i’ve been in a lunch rut so this week I’m focusing on nutrient rich lunches that get my tastebuds excited and nourish my gut health as well 🫶🏼

Ingredients (serves 2):
- 2 outdoor bred sausages
- 1 small onion
- 1 garlic clove
- 1/2 bell pepper 
- 1/4 butternut squash
- 1 cup of green beans
- 1 tsp sea salt
- 1 tsp oregano
- 1 tsp smoked paprika
- 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 1 can cooked green lentils (drained)

How to:
1. Brown the sausages in olive oil.
2. Remove and add the onions and garlic and cook for a few minutes until soft and slightly caramelised.
3. Chop the sausages into bite sized pieces and add back to the pan along with the rest of the ingredients.
4. Top with 400ml of water, cover and leave to simmer for 10 minutes.
5. Serve with fresh herbs, chilli flakes and cracked black pepper.

What I ate today as a nutritionist 🫶🏼

BREAKFAST: I love starting the day with fats! Today I did a banana and spinach smoothie with healthy fats from coconut milk, kefir and flax seeds to regulate blood sugars and my nervous system.

MORNING: later in the morning I had a matcha almond milk latte. Matcha is more gentle than coffee so doesn’t give me the jitters!

LUNCH: today was leftovers of smoky sausage and lentil soup which is full of fibre and veggies for gut health.

AFTERNOON: it’s this time of day where I love something sweet. Today I did a simple full fat yoghurt bowl topped with frozen raspberries, hemp seeds and raw honey.

DINNER: this is usually a batch cooked meal I made on the weekend before and tonight i went for homemade chicken tikka masala with fluffy brown rice and green beans.

EVENING: to end the day I always have a relaxing herbal tea with a few pieces of dark chocolate and nuts for blood sugar balance.

hopefully this gives some food inspiration 🤍

GUT HEALTH BASICS 📝 when i was experiencing daily bloat, brain fog, panic, stomach pain, breakouts and skin rashes I felt so overwhelmed with how to start healing myself. now looking back there are some key points to follow in order to improve gut health and start feeling better. so if you’re in the same boat I’m really hoping that this simple list acts as a starting point for you 😘 
#strengthandsalad

GUT HEALTH LUNCH INSPO 🍜 as someone who has battled leaky gut and various other digestive issues, discovering recipes that were easy on my gut and that I actually wanted to eat was super important in the success of my healing! I found easy bowls that were rich in healing broths, nutrient dense ingredients and gut-loving fermented foods became my go-to. I still like to have meals like this a few times a week to keep on top of my gut health and continue making me feel nourished 🥰

Serves 1 / takes 5 minutes
• 1 tsp miso
• 1 tbsp tamari
• 300ml broth (I like beef bone broth but any high quality stock will work)
• few sheets of seaweed
• 1 nest of rice noodles (about 50g)
• 2 heaped tbsp kimchi
• large handful of spinach and/or rocket
• 100g organic tofu (cubed)
• black sesame seeds

1. In a pan add the miso, tamari and stock and heat through.
2. Add the rest of the ingredients stir well, cover and leave for a few minutes until noodles are soft.
3. Pour into your favourite bowl and slurp away!

Enjoy! #strengthandsalad

whoever said pancakes for breakfast can’t be healthy hasn’t had these 🤝🏼 some tips: 1. i always serve with a large dollop of full fat yoghurt to reduce the blood sugar spike from the fruit and maple syrup. 2. i use an oat or rice flour for extra fibre! 3. adding super-fruits like blueberries adds tonnes of nutrients for skin health and cell protection 🫶🏼

makes 12 medium pancakes👇🏼

wet ingredients:
2 medium ripe bananas (mashed)
2 eggs
1/2 cup almond milk
2 tbsp olive oil 

dry ingredients:
1.5 cups flour (I used a rice and oat blend)
1 tsp cinnamon
2 tsp baking powder
pinch of sea salt

other:
large handful of blueberries
yoghurt (I like @fage 5%)
maple syrup

How to:
1. mix all wet ingredients in a large bowl with a fork
2. add the dry ingredients and mix again until smooth
3. gently stir in the blueberries and heat a small amount of olive oil in a pan on a medium heat
4. add about 1/4 cup of the batter, flipping after about 30 seconds
5. repeat until the mix is gone
6. i eat 4-5 pancakes per serving and freeze leftovers for easy breakfasts another day 🥰

hope you enjoy! #strengthandsalad

Let’s talk about acne 👉🏼 for those who don’t know, I struggled with regular breakouts for a couple of years. I’d never experienced breakouts in my life, so I felt frustrated to suddenly have them in my 30s and my confidence definitely took a hit. Luckily around this time I began studying for my nutrition degree where I learnt all about the power of diet and lifestyle to heal skin issues for good! I addressed my root causes (which for me were emotional stress and an omega 3 and vitamin d deficiency!), worked on some diet changes and adopted more self care into my routine. 3 years on I’m still surprised everyday when I look in the mirror and see healthy clear skin 😌. This worked for me and I really hope these tips help you too ❤️

SEA SALT CHOC ENERGY BARS 🍫 sharing one of my favourite recipes to include in client nutrition plans (and what I make for myself each week too!). these genuinely leave you feeling SO satisfied, and are ideal if you’re looking to swap processed sugary foods for a more natural alternative, improve gut health, nourish hormones and increase energy 🥰

ingredients: 
- 1 cup rolled oats
- 1/2 cup peanut butter
- 1/3 cup honey
- 1/2 cup shredded coconut (unsweetened)
- 1/4 cup flaxseed
- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
- 100g very dark chocolate (80-90%)
- 1 tbsp coconut oil
- flaky sea salt (i like maldon) (for topping)

how to make:
1. Mix everything in a large bowl.
2. Line a tin and add the mix, patting firmly. 
3. Put in the freezer for 15 minutes.
4. Melt the dark chocolate and coconut oil and pour on top of the mix and sprinkle with flaky sea salt.
5. Put in the freezer again for 30 minutes.
6. Once hard cut into 8 bars and store in an airtight container in the fridge for up to a week.

CYCLE SYNCING SHOPPING LIST 📝 as someone who’s had a history of irregular periods and hormonal imbalances I’ve been getting back into cycle syncing over the last few months and I’m definitely noticing the benefits.

Each part of our menstrual cycle is like a season and it needs supporting in its own special way:
• the Menstrual period is like winter where our body craves iron rich replenishing meals
• the Follicular phase is like spring, so think light and fresh foods
• Ovulation is the body’s summer so foods packed with healthy fats help us thrive
• and finally the Luteal phase is most like autumn where cooked foods help us feel nourished

Giving my body the right nutrients at the right time means I’m having regular 30 day cycles, healthier bleeds, little to no pms and increased energy! So add these foods to your grocery basket for better fertility and a healthier cycle 🫶🏼 #strengthandsalad

GUT FRIENDLY MEAL IDEAS 👉🏼 i’ve been struggling with knowing what to eat lately so this weekend I mapped out a whole new meal plan for myself that’s full of gut healthy foods that I'm actually excited to cook + eat! i’ll use this as a basis for my grocery lists and as always, each meal is balanced and packed with nutrients for better digestive health 🤌🏼. 
 
breakfasts:
- chia seed pudding, berries, nut butter, raw honey
- eggs on sourdough with pesto, avocado + garlic tomatoes
- gut soothing smoothie with greens, kefir + dates
- overnight oats with greek yoghurt, banana and chopped walnuts
 
easy lunches:
- roasted sweet potato salad with lemon tahini dressing
- sesame ginger chicken salad
- tofu noodle ramen made with bone broth
- dinner leftovers
 
snacks:
- kimchi, veg sticks and hummus
- chocolate orange stuffed dates
- salted chocolate energy bars
- whipped cottage cheese, berries and raw honey
 
batch-cook & quick dinners:
- tofu tikka masala with a side of greens
- mexican beef and red pepper stew
- pan-fried salmon with balsamic roasted veggies
- chicken peanut curry with sticky rice and green beans

hope this gives you some inspiration too 🥰 #strengthandsalad

GUT-HEALTHY BATCH COOK MEAL: creamy lamb + chickpea korma with a cucumber lemon salad 🍋. you probably know by now that batch cooking is my favourite hack for stress free meals - and this one is a winner! all of the prep is done in 15 minutes, it’s high in protein (which is great for gut repair) and so full of flavour too 🤌🏼.

Serves 6 // freeze leftovers for quick meals

creamy lamb & chickpea korma:
- 500g frozen veg mix of onions, carrots + celery (this saves so much time!)
- 1 tsp pre-chopped frozen ginger
- 2 tsp pre-chopped frozen garlic
- 2 tbsp korma paste (@meridianfoods has good ingredients)
- 1 tsp sea salt 
- 1 tbsp cumin
- 1/2 tbsp ground coriander
- 1 tsp turmeric 
- 500g diced lamb
- 1 tin chickpeas
- 50g sultanas
- 400ml water
- 100g yoghurt 

for the cucumber salad:
- 1/4 cucumber
- 1 tbsp olive oil
- juice of 1/2 lemon
- 1/4 tsp sea salt
- few cracks of black pepper 

How to make:
1. Sweat the veg mix, garlic and ginger in a 1 tbsp olive oil for 5 minutes.
2. Add the lamb and cook for another 5 minutes stirring frequently to brown the lamb.
3. Add everything else apart from the yoghurt and mix well.
4. Leave to simmer for an hour to allow the lamb to soften and all the flavours to develop!
5. Before serving stir in the yoghurt and mix the salad ingredients and set aside.
6. Plate everything up and serve with fluffy quinoa or brown rice for a complete meal.

enjoy 🥰 #strengthandsalad

QUIZ: HOW HEALTHY IS YOUR GUT? 📝 the number one question I had when I first started hearing about gut health was “how do I know if my gut is healthy?” so i created this handy quiz so that you can assess your own digestive health and find the support that you need 🫶🏼 #strengthandsalad

nurturing my gut, one grocery haul at a time! 🛒 sharing my weekly go-to shopping list for happy digestion and gut-friendly goodness. i always focus on fiber-packed carbs, nutrient dense proteins, probiotic-rich yoghurt, and colourful veggies so that my gut microbiome can thrive! these goodies will make you feel amazing from the inside out. hope this gives you some healthy inspiration! 🥑🥕🍏

even on busy mornings i make sure to fuel my gut with a nourishing breakfast. it sets the tone for the day, balances energy, and makes me feel good. here’s a week of gut-friendly breakfasts that take just 5 minutes to make 🫶🏼

1. parsley & cheddar omelette with sourdough and antioxidant rich berries
2. chia pudding, fresh berries and crunchy peanut butter
3. hot sauce scramble with sweet banana & pb sourdough toast
4. green gut calming smoothie made with spinach, pineapple, oats, chia seeds, almond milk and magnesium
5. probiotic yoghurt bowl with flax seeds, pumpkin and sunflower seeds, berries, and raw honey 
6. burrata, rocket and dill toast with a fried egg
7. creamy fibre oats with probiotic yoghurt, homemade chia jam and cinnamon 

#strengthandsalad

add this to your list of easy weeknight meals that are loaded with gut healing veggies, nourishing omega 3s and full of flavour too ✔️🍽️

Serves 4 // 20 minutes 

• 3 salmon fillets, skin off
• 2 tsps olive oil
• 2 tbsps butter
• 1 tbsp garlic, diced
• 1 small onion, diced
• 200ml stock
• 150g jar of sundried tomato, drained
• 100g cherry tomatoes
• 1 medium courgette, cubed
• 4 heaped tbsps yoghurt
• 3 handfuls spinach
• 1/2 cup parmesan, grated
• 1 tbsp parsley, chopped
 
1. Pan fry the salmon in olive oil until cooked through (about 5-6 minutes)
2. Remove from the pan and add the butter, garlic and onion and fry for a few minutes
3. Add the stock, tomatoes and courgette and cook for 5-7 minutes until soft
4. Add the remaining ingredients, stir well and simmer for a minute then take off the heat
5.  Serve with quinoa, brown rice or pasta

enjoy 🫶🏼 #strengthandsalad

4-INGREDIENT COTTAGE CHEESE & SPINACH OMELETTE 🍳 starting the week with a quick and delicious high-protein breakfast! most of us know that protein is great for building muscle but it’s also amazing for gut health because it maintains a healthy gut lining and beneficial gut bacteria too which improves mood, skin quality and digestion 🤌🏼

• 3 large eggs (I use @clarence_court)
• Handful of spinach (chopped)
• 1 small garlic clove (minced)
• 3 tbsps full fat cottage cheese

1. Over a medium heat fry the garlic and spinach in olive oil for 30 seconds.
2. Add the eggs and cover until firm and cooked (about 3 minutes).
3. Once cooked add the cottage cheese and top with salt, pepper and a drizzle of olive oil. 

hope you love this one as much as me 🥰 #strengthandsalad

for the longest time I was constantly bloated and uncomfortable. choosing clothes, exercising and socialising almost became impossible until one day i got curious about WHY i was always bloated. i was on a mission to heal my gut and along the way I learnt that there are some key causes to chronic bloating, all of which are fixable! so I'm here to tell you that with the right knowledge and choices change is possible! 🫶🏼 #strengthandsalad

I’m always looking for ways to sneak in some extra gut health self-care into my daily schedule and the commute to the office is the perfect place 👍🏼

1. water on-the-go
hydration is key for a happy gut! and when you arrive at the office you've already made a good dent in your water goal - win win!

2. fibre rich snack
i've found this the most useful if i'm running late or get stuck in traffic. something simple like raw nuts and fruit provide plenty of gut health nutrients and balance blood sugars too.

3. gut health podcast
i truly believe that knowledge is power so optimising your commute time to learn how to better look after yourself is an act of self-care.

4. breathing
deep diaphragmatic breathing delivers oxygen, nutrients and gently massages the digestive tract making it super helpful for gut health.

5. stretching
light stretching has a similar effect to breathing and reduces tension and stress which is a game changer for gut health.

hope these tips are helpful :) #strengthandsalad

trying to up my breakfast game with more variety, protein and FLAVOUR, whilst still supporting healthy digestion - this certainly did all that 🤌🏼

COTTAGE CHEESE & BLISTERED TOMS ON SEEDED SOURDOUGH 

- 10 cherry tomatoes (gut cell protection)
- 1 tbsp olive oil (anti-inflammatory)
- 1 garlic clove, minced (gut balancing)
- 1 tsp oregano (gut soothing)
- 1/4 tsp salt + pepper 
- 3 heaped tbsp natural cottage cheese (good protein source)
- sourdough (prebiotic fibre)

How to: heat oil in pan, add the tomatoes, garlic, salt, pepper and oregano and cook until tomatoes can be squashed with the back of a spoon (around 5 minutes). toast your sourdough and layer with cottage cheese, tomatoes, extra olive oil and salt and pepper if desired. enjoy 🫶🏼 #strengthandsalad

creamy miso butternut squash soup 🍂 full of nutrients to nourish the gut barrier and promote healthy skin!

- 1 onion
- 2 garlic cloves
- 1 tsp ginger
- 1 tsp turmeric 
- 1 tsp sea salt
- 1 medium butternut squash 
- 1 medium sweet potato
- 1 medium carrot
- 1 litre bone broth (or any stock)
- 1 tin coconut milk
- 2 tbsp miso
- 50g parmesan
- few cracks black pepper

this makes a huge batch for ready made lunches or dinners, enjoy! ❤️ #strengthandsalad
